<p><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">As the author with the current longest title on the mainlist, I feel personally attacked by this.</span> no longer the case</p>
<p>+1</p>
<hr />
<p>When I was ten, I was working on a project in school. As I peered over the project of a partner, I saw the face of beloved Hanna-Barbera character Speedy Gonzalez on the computer screen across from me. Not knowing much about the character, I asked my classmate &quot;Oh, he's from Yogi Bear, right?&quot;</p>
<p>My classmate turned to me and said, &quot;Yogi Bear isn't real.&quot;</p>
<p>For the life of me, and to this day, I am still baffled by what he meant by that. While yes, Yogi Bear is not real, how does that reply answer my question? Under what circumstances is Speedy Gonzalez real, while Yogi Bear is not? Did my classmate think that Speedy Gonzalez was a real mouse that lived in Mexico? I struggle with these questions every day of my life, but I do not have the courage to ask him what he meant. It has been far too long, in any case.</p>
<p>I would like to imagine my classmate is the creator of SCP-2000 portrayed in this article.</p>

